The paper deals with lower bounds on the mim-width of certain graph classes, which is a measure of graph complexity that has seen applications in graph algorithms and problems related to propositional satisfiability. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories related to graph theory and algorithms, such as cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Among these, cs.DM and cs.DS seem the most likely, as they are more directly related to graph theory and algorithms, while cs.CG and cs.LG are more focused on geometric and machine learning aspects of graph theory, respectively. Cs.CC is also a possibility, as it deals with the computational complexity of graph algorithms.
